The curate was inclined to adopt the manners of ſuch great examples—but, ſelf-intereſt, ſome affection to Rebecca, and concern for the character of his family, made him wiſh to talk a little with Henry; who now repeated what he had ſaid reſpecting his marriage with Rebecca, and promiſed "to come the very next day in ſecret, and deliver her from the care of the infant; 
                           〈◊〉
                         the ſuſpicion that would attend her nurſing it."
